xmode.content:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

# Sample data
# Assuming we have a DataFrame `df` with columns 'genre' and 'year'
data = {
    'genre': ['Impressionism', 'Renaissance', 'Baroque', 'Cubism'],
    'year': [1872, 1503, 1600, 1907]
}
df = pd.DataFrame(data)

# Find the oldest painting year per genre
genre_oldest_year = df.groupby('genre')['year'].min()

# Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
genre_oldest_year.plot(kind='bar', color='skyblue')
plt.title('Year of the Oldest Painting per Genre')
plt.xlabel('Genre')
plt.ylabel('Year')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()

# Save the plot
plt.savefig('/home/ubuntu/workspace/XMODE-LLMCompiler/ceasura_langgraph/experiments/log//9/plot-out.png')
plt.close()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from collections import defaultdict

# Data
paintings = [
    {'genre': 'Hodegetria', 'movement': 'Renaissance', 'painting_count': 1},
    {'genre': 'allegory', 'movement': 'neoclassicism', 'painting_count': 3},
    {'genre': 'figure painting', 'movement': 'neoclassicism', 'painting_count': 3},
    {'genre': 'genre art', 'movement': 'neoclassicism', 'painting_count': 1},
    {'genre': 'history painting', 'movement': 'Renaissance', 'painting_count': 1},
    {'genre': 'history painting', 'movement': 'neoclassicism', 'painting_count': 9},
    {'genre': 'interior view', 'movement': 'neoclassicism', 'painting_count': 1},
    {'genre': 'mythological painting', 'movement': 'neoclassicism', 'painting_count': 4},
    {'genre': 'nude', 'movement': 'neoclassicism', 'painting_count': 8},
    {'genre': 'portrait', 'movement': 'Renaissance', 'painting_count': 9},
    {'genre': 'portrait', 'movement': 'neoclassicism', 'painting_count': 7},
    {'genre': 'religious art', 'movement': 'Renaissance', 'painting_count': 54}
]

# Aggregate painting counts by movement
movement_counts = defaultdict(int)
for painting in paintings:
    movement_counts[painting['movement']] += painting['painting_count']

# Prepare data for plotting
movements = list(movement_counts.keys())
counts = list(movement_counts.values())

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.bar(movements, counts, color=['blue', 'green'])
plt.title('Count of Paintings in Each Movement')
plt.xlabel('Art Movement')
plt.ylabel('Number of Paintings')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()

# Save the plot
plt.savefig('/home/ubuntu/workspace/XMODE-LLMCompiler/ceasura_langgraph/experiments/log/26/plot-out.png')
plt.close()

args.question: Prepare data for plotting the number of paintings for each year.

xmode.name: data_preparation

xmode.content:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Data
years = ['1438', '1470', '1472', '1474', '1475', '1476', '1477', '1479', '1480', '1483', '1500', '1520', '1525', '1528', '1530', '1536', '1550', '1565', '1583', '1585', '1600', '1764', '1770', '1771', '1784', '1785', '1787', '1788', '1789', '1793', '1799', '1800', '1806', '1811', '1814', '1824', '1827', '1840', '1856', '1862', '1879', '2000']
number_of_paintings = [1, 2, 1, 1, 1, 2, 13, 12, 3, 4, 3, 1, 1, 1, 2, 7, 1, 2, 1, 1, 4, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, 2, 2, 2, 1, 1, 2, 2, 1, 2, 1, 1, 9, 2, 2, 1]

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.bar(years, number_of_paintings, color='skyblue')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Number of Paintings')
plt.title('Number of Paintings per Year')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.tight_layout()

# Save the plot
plt.savefig('/home/ubuntu/workspace/XMODE-LLMCompiler/ceasura_langgraph/experiments/log/29/number_of_paintings_per_year.png')
plt.close()
